      "writtenOn": "2019-10-08T18:45:41Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hrm, yeah. I\u0027d rather not modify os.Environ, but maybe we could add functionality to go/exec to search the given PATH for the executable rather than relying on os.Environ.\n\nAnother option for this particular use case is just:\n\ndocker.go:\n\nvar docker \u003d \"docker\"\n\ndocker_test.go:\n\n...\n  docker \u003d \"/path/to/test_bin\"\n...\n\nIf we were worried about conflicts we could do something like:\n\ntype Docker string\n\nvar DefaultDocker \u003d \"docker\"\n\nfunc (d *Docker) Build() ...",
